
Verify a module's existence is to do:

bash-4.4# perl -MDate::Calc -e 1

bash-4.4# cpan install Date::Calc

bash-4.4# perl -MDate::DateTime -e 1

bash-4.4# cpan install DateTime

Local Modules perl.pm:
/usr/share/perl5/Date/
/usr/lib64/perl5/Date/

http://ftp.devil-linux.org/pub/devel/sources/1.2/perl-ext/Date-Calc-5.4.tar.gz
http://ftp.riken.jp/Linux/mandrake/devel/cooker/SRPMS/main/release/perl-Date-Calc-6.300.0-5.src.rpm
http://ftp.riken.jp/Linux/mandrake/devel/cooker/SRPMS/main/release/perl-DateTime-TimeZone-1.270.0-4.src.rpm

rpm -ivh perl-Date-Calc-6.300.0-5.src.rpm
rpm -ivh perl-DateTime-TimeZone-1.270.0-4.src.rpm